26/03/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha met on Tuesday (March 25th) with Ali Ahmeti, leader of the Democratic Union for Integration, the largest ethnic Albanian party in Macedonia.
They discussed the latest political developments in the region, as well as their countries' bids for invitations to NATO membership, which they hope to receive at the Alliance's summit in Bucharest next week.
Ahmeti also met with Albanian Parliament Speaker Josefina Topalli.
(Shekulli, Kohajone -26/03/08;
Albanian Prime Minister, BalkanWeb, Top-Channel, Makfax - 25/03/08)
